Three men, Sodiq Raman (47), Oyetunji Oyekan (35) and Akeem Balogun (31), were on arraigned before an Ikeja magistratesâ€™ court for stealing a necklace worth N3 million. The three pleaded not guilty to the charges of conspiracy, illegal possession of firearms and stealing. The Magistrate, Mrs R. A. Alejo, gave the defendants bail of one N1m each with two sureties each as part of the bail conditions. Earlier, the prosecutor, Sgt Olasunkanmi Adejumola, told the court that the defendants and others at large committed the offences on December 15, 2021, at 10pm at Ado Langbasa, Ajah, Lagos State. The judge adjourned the case to February 16. (NAN)